		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Decision theory</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<p><b>Decision theory</b> in <a href="/wiki/Mathematics" title="Mathematics">mathematics</a> and <a href="/wiki/Statistics" title="Statistics">statistics</a> is concerned with identifying the <a href="/wiki/Value" title="Value">values</a>, <a href="/wiki/Uncertainty" title="Uncertainty">uncertainties</a> and other issues relevant in a given <a href="/wiki/Decision_making" title="Decision making">decision</a> and the resulting <a href="/wiki/Optimal_decision" title="Optimal decision">optimal decision</a>. It is sometimes called <a href="/wiki/Game_theory" title="Game theory">game theory</a>.</p>
